{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Hyperparameter Optimization\n",
    "\n",
    "## CircuitBench Tutorial 6\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates systematic hyperparameter optimization for surrogate machine learning models using reproducible search strategies and cross-validation.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Learning Objectives\n",
    "\n",
    "- Load benchmark datasets\n",
    "- Define hyperparameter search spaces\n",
    "- Perform Grid Search\n",
    "- Perform Random Search\n",
    "- Compare optimized models\n",
    "- Analyze optimization results\n",
    "- Export reproducible reports\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Scientific Background\n",
    "\n",
    "Hyperparameter optimization is essential for obtaining optimal predictive performance while avoiding overfitting. CircuitBench supports reproducible optimization workflows using cross-validation and standardized evaluation metrics."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import random\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "\n",
    "import json\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")\n",
    "\n",
    "SEED = 42\n",
    "random.seed(SEED)\n",
    "np.random.seed(SEED)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import RandomizedSearchCV\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from circuitbench.benchmark import BenchmarkRunner"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Load Benchmark Dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "runner = BenchmarkRunner()\n",
    "benchmark = runner.load(\"CMOS_Inverter\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Prepare Training Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_train = benchmark.X_train\n",
    "y_train = benchmark.y_train\n",
    "\n",
    "X_test = benchmark.X_test\n",
    "y_test = benchmark.y_test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Define Baseline Model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "10",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model = RandomForestRegressor(random_state=SEED)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "11",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Hyperparameter Search Space"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "12",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "parameter_grid = {\n",
    "    \"n_estimators\": [50, 100, 200, 500],\n",
    "    \"max_depth\": [None, 5, 10, 20],\n",
    "    \"min_samples_split\": [2, 5, 10],\n",
    "    \"min_samples_leaf\": [1, 2, 4],\n",
    "    \"max_features\": [\"sqrt\", \"log2\"],\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "parameter_grid"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "13",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Grid Search Optimization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "14",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "grid_search = GridSearchCV(\n",
    "    estimator=model,\n",
    "    param_grid=parameter_grid,\n",
    "    scoring=\"neg_root_mean_squared_error\",\n",
    "    cv=5,\n",
    "    n_jobs=-1,\n",
    "    verbose=1,\n",
    "    return_train_score=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "15",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Best Grid Search Parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "16",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "grid_search.best_params_"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "17",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Best Grid Search Score"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "18",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "grid_search.best_score_"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "19",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Random Search Optimization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "20",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "random_search = RandomizedSearchCV(\n",
    "    estimator=model,\n",
    "    param_distributions=parameter_grid,\n",
    "    n_iter=25,\n",
    "    scoring=\"neg_root_mean_squared_error\",\n",
    "    cv=5,\n",
    "    random_state=SEED,\n",
    "    n_jobs=-1,\n",
    "    verbose=1,\n",
    "    return_train_score=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "random_search.fit(X_train, y_train)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "21",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Best Random Search Parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "22",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "random_search.best_params_"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "23",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Compare Optimization Strategies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "24",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "comparison = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        \"Method\": [\"Grid Search\", \"Random Search\"],\n",
    "        \"Best Score\": [grid_search.best_score_, random_search.best_score_],\n",
    "    }\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "comparison"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "25",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Save Optimization Summary"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "26",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "output_dir = Path(\"hyperparameter_results\")\n",
    "output_dir.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "comparison.to_csv(output_dir / \"optimization_comparison.csv\", index=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "27",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Evaluate Optimized Models"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "28",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "grid_predictions = grid_search.best_estimator_.predict(X_test)\n",
    "random_predictions = random_search.best_estimator_.predict(X_test)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "29",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Test Set Performance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "30",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "results = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        \"Method\": [\"Grid Search\", \"Random Search\"],\n",
    "        \"RMSE\": [\n",
    "            np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, grid_predictions)),\n",
    "            np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, random_predictions)),\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "    }\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "31",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Optimization Performance Comparison"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "32",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "plt.bar(results[\"Method\"], results[\"RMSE\"])\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"RMSE\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Hyperparameter Optimization Performance\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "33",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cross-Validation Results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "34",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cv_results = pd.DataFrame(grid_search.cv_results_)\n",
    "\n",
    "cv_results.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "35",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Top 10 Hyperparameter Configurations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "36",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "top_configs = cv_results.sort_values(by=\"rank_test_score\").head(10)\n",
    "\n",
    "top_configs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "37",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Export Cross-Validation Results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "38",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cv_results.to_csv(output_dir / \"grid_search_cv_results.csv\", index=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "39",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Export Optimization Report"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "40",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "report = {\n",
    "    \"best_method\": (\n",
    "        \"Grid Search\"\n",
    "        if grid_search.best_score_ >= random_search.best_score_\n",
    "        else \"Random Search\"\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    \"grid_best_score\": float(grid_search.best_score_),\n",
    "    \"random_best_score\": float(random_search.best_score_),\n",
    "    \"grid_best_parameters\": grid_search.best_params_,\n",
    "    \"random_best_parameters\": random_search.best_params_,\n",
    "    \"random_seed\": SEED,\n",
    "}\n"
    "with open(output_dir / \"optimization_report.json\", \"w\") as f:\n",
    "    json.dump(report, f, indent=4)"
   ]
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "41",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Reproducibility Checklist\n",
    "\n",
    "- Fixed random seed used for all optimization experiments.\n",
    "- Hyperparameter search space fully documented.\n",
    "- Five-fold cross-validation applied consistently.\n",
    "- Optimization results exported.\n",
    "- Best hyperparameters recorded.\n",
    "- Cross-validation statistics archived.\n",
    "- Optimization report saved in JSON format.\n"
   ]
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "42",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Best Practices\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Evaluate optimized models on an independent test set.\n",
    "2. Use cross-validation to reduce selection bias.\n",
    "3. Record all search spaces and optimization settings.\n",
    "4. Compare multiple optimization strategies.\n",
    "5. Save optimization artifacts for reproducibility.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "43",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Next Notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "Continue with **7_SHAP_Explainability.ipynb** to interpret surrogate models using SHAP values, feature attribution, local explanations, and publication-quality explainable AI visualizations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "44",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook we:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Defined a reproducible hyperparameter search space.\n",
    "- Optimized a Random Forest surrogate model using Grid Search and Random Search.\n",
    "- Compared optimization strategies through cross-validation.\n",
    "- Evaluated optimized models on an independent test set.\n",
    "- Exported optimization results, cross-validation statistics, and benchmark reports.\n",
    "\n",
    "These procedures provide a rigorous and reproducible framework for hyperparameter optimization within CircuitBench."
   ]
  }
 ],
